{
  "texts": [
    "We identify linguistic features associated with each core framing task by calculating the log-odds ratio with informative Dirichlet prior within each issue area (Monroe et al., 2008).",
    "This metric identifies features that are statistically overrepresented in one corpus relative to another.",
    "For example, we compare the frequencies of linguistic features in diagnostic tweets about immigration to frequencies in all tweets about immigration.",
    "We calculate log-odds statistics for five linguistic features: words, verbs, adjectives, subjectverb pairs, and verb-object pairs.",
    "Our consideration of subject, verb, and object relations is inspired by Johnston and Alimi (2013), who argues that these structures are meaningful units for social movement frame analysis."
  ]
}